post-fertilization, not at \u003Cstrong\u003E30 days\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003E100 days\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003E34 days\u003C/strong\u003E, or \u003Cstrong\u003E5 days\u003C/strong\u003E. The development starts as an endodermal thickening in the floor of the primitive pharynx, between the first and second pharyngeal pouches in an area that will become the foramen caecum of the tongue.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe thyroid primordium then proliferates, elongates, and migrates caudally as a bilobed diverticulum. By week 7, the thyroid reaches its final position in the neck, anterior to the trachea. The gland remains connected to the tongue by the thyroglossal duct, which normally degenerates by week 8.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The thyroid gland begins developing at 24 days post-fertilization from the floor of the primitive pharynx.","The thyroid primordium forms as an endodermal thickening in the foramen caecum between the first and second pharyngeal pouches."],"references":["Moran C, Schoenmakers N, Visser WE, Schoenmakers E, Agostini M, Chatterjee K. Genetic disorders of thyroid development, hormone biosynthesis and signalling. Clin Endocrinol (Oxf). 2022 Oct;97(4):502-514. doi: 10.1111/cen.14817. Epub 2022 Sep 5. PMID: 35999191; PMCID: PMC9544560.","Rosen RD, Sapra A. Embryology, Thyroid. [Updated 2023 May 1]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK551611/","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine System E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Wass, J. A., \u0026 Stewa